== Example of non-uniqueness ==
To understand uniqueness of solutions, contrast the following two examples of first order ordinary differential equations for . Both differential equations will possess a single stationary point 

First, the homogeneous linear equation (formula_39), a stationary solution is , which is obtained for the initial condition . Beginning with any other initial condition , the solution formula_40 tends toward the stationary point , but it only approaches it in the limit of infinite time, so the uniqueness of solutions over all finite times is guaranteed. 

By contrast for an equation in which the stationary point can be reached after a &quot;finite&quot; time, uniqueness of solutions does not hold. Consider the homogeneous nonlinear equation , which has at least these two solutions corresponding to the initial condition : and 

