so the previous state of the system is not uniquely determined by its state at or after &quot;t&quot; = 0. The uniqueness theorem does not apply because the derivative of the function is not bounded in the neighborhood of and therefore it is not Lipschitz continuous, violating the hypothesis of the theorem.

